Class Utils

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.trajano.auth.internal.Utils

  • public final class Utils
extends Object
    Utility methods. Normally these would be in a separate JAR file like commons-lang, but to prevent complications during installation such as requiring to install additional JAR files, this class was created.

    • Method Detail

      • getJwsPayload

        public static byte[] getJwsPayload(String serialization,
                   JsonWebKeySet keyset)
                            throws GeneralSecurityException
        Gets the JWS Payload from a JWS Compact Serialization. The validation follows the rules in Message Signature or MAC validation section of JSON Web Signature.

        Note that "jku", "jwk", "x5u" and "x5c" should nor will never be implemented. It does not make sense for the serialization to contain its own validation.

        Parameters:
        serialization - JWS compact serialization
        keyset - JSON web key used to validate the token
        Returns:
        the JWS payload
        Throws:
        GeneralSecurityException - problem with crypto APIs or signature was not valid
